# Integration Tests

This directory contains the integration test suite for `{{SERVICE_NAME}}`.

## Running locally

```bash
# Start the lab and run tests
make test-local

# Tear down
make test-clean
```

## Lab topology

| Container | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `mysql` | MySQL 8 on tmpfs — fast CREATE/DROP |
| `redis` | Redis 7 |
| `wiremock` | Downstream HTTP stubs |
| `{{SERVICE_NAME}}-coverage` | Service binary with -cover for coverage merge |
| `test-runner` | Executes `go test ./tests/...` |

## Writing tests

Use `testkit/httpx.NewServiceClient` for HTTP assertions:

```go
import "github.com/phona/sisyphus/testkit/httpx"

func TestMyEndpoint(t *testing.T) {
    client := httpx.NewServiceClient(env.GetEnv("SERVICE_URL", "http://localhost:{{SERVICE_PORT}}"))
    resp := client.Post(t, "/api/v1/resource", map[string]any{"key": "value"})
    resp.AssertCreated(t).AssertSuccess(t)
}
```

## Coverage

Coverage data is written to `tests/coverage/`. Merge and fix paths for SonarQube:

```bash
go tool covdata textfmt -i tests/coverage -o coverage.out
./testkit/scripts/fix-coverage-paths.sh coverage.out main/go.mod
```

## Stub priority

WireMock stubs are in `tests/wiremock/mappings/`. Lower priority number = matched first.
Use `priority: 1` for exact-match stubs; leave default (5) for catch-all fallbacks.
